<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-23T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-23T06:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3307: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-23T19:00:00+08:00">December 23, 1931—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 23—6:44 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1125. The Consul at Dairen reports on December 22, 4 p.m., as follows:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Japanese military authorities there are commandeering auto trucks
                                    on an extensive scale and shipping them northward.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>The Consul General at Mukden reports on December 22, 10 p.m., as follows:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>That afternoon trucks loaded with boxes marked “shrapnel” were
                                    observed en route to the railway. Taken in conjunction with the
                                    Dairen report mentioned above, this would indicate that the
                                    anticipated drive by Japanese troops westward is imminent.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
